  "poem": {
    "content": "The cabin whispers, damp and old,\nA place where weary stories fold.\nRetire here, by the crystal lake,\nWatch sunlight new awaken break.\n\nWelcome, traveler, jump the gate,\nLeave behind the sting of fate.\nThe valve within, release the strain,\nRebuild your heart, begin again.\n\nNo glory sought, no bitter need,\nJust ethics planted, like a seed.\nA brush of wind across the face,\nFind comfort in this quiet place.\n\nCoffee steams, a fragrant art,\nA solace to a weary heart.\nFruit hangs heavy, ripe and sweet,\nA style of living, incomplete?\n\nThe damp earth sighs, a gentle plea,\nFor understanding, wild and free.\nThis lake-glass holds a truth unseen,\nA vibrant, tranquil, hopeful sheen.",
